newsitem.title: USA: Tel Offshore says units delisted.
newsitem.headline: Tel Offshore says units delisted.

text.p: Tel Offshore Trust said its units have been delisted by Nasdaq's SmallCap Market after it was denied a waiver of asset requirement rules.
The company said last month that its units were slated to be delisted because the trust no longer met Nasdaq's total asset requirement.
Tel Offshore said a Nasdaq panel determined that the trust would be unable to sustain long term compliance with Nasdaq continued listing standards.
Tel Offshore said it has been advised by Nasdaq that the trust units may be eligible for trading on the OTC Bulletin Board.
